Resolution Description: The Department of Transportation inspected this complaint and repaired the problem.
The Police Department responded to the complaint and took action to fix the condition.

Descriptor: Branch or Limb Has Fallen Down
Resolution Description: The Department of Parks and Recreation has corrected the condition.

Agency Name: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene
Resolution Description: The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene has determined that the reported incident is isolated.  They will inspect the location according to its normal schedule for sanitary inspections. You can provide more information in a new Service Request by calling 311 or going online to www.nyc.gov/311.

The Department of Consumer Affairs mailed you a complaint form. If you received the form and have not yet completed it, please do so. Be sure to follow the instructions on the form and return it to DCA with all required documentation.     311 can assist those who have not received the complaint form by creating a new Service Request. Additionally, 311 can assist those who returned the form but want to inquire about the status of the filed complaint.
